Task: Build a high-performance, data-rich Dashboard for the Corefinity Control Panel.
вЂ‹1. Global Stats Overview (Cards):
вЂ‹Create 4 summary cards at the top:
вЂ‹Total Environments: (e.g., 12)
вЂ‹Active Deployments: (e.g., 3 - with a pulsing green dot)
вЂ‹Pending Tickets: (e.g., 5 - colored in brand-orange)
вЂ‹System Health: (e.g., 99.9% - with a small sparkline chart)
вЂ‹2. Environment Health Monitoring:
вЂ‹Create a "Top Environments" table.
вЂ‹Features: Use the OrangeLink for names. Include a "mini-gauge" or progress bar for CPU/Memory usage.
вЂ‹Interactive Data: Use a setInterval to make these metrics fluctuate by 1-2% every few seconds so the dashboard feels "live."
вЂ‹3. Recent Activity Feed:
вЂ‹Create a vertical timeline on the right side (or below) showing recent events:
вЂ‹"Deployment Successful for corefinity-api (main branch)"
вЂ‹"New Support Ticket created: #4029"
вЂ‹"Firewall Rule Added: 192.161.x.x"
вЂ‹Use icons from lucide-react to distinguish activity types (Check circle for deployments, Message for tickets, Shield for firewall).
вЂ‹4. Quick Actions Panel:
вЂ‹Add a sidebar or section with "One-Click" buttons:
вЂ‹Create New Environment (Primary Orange Button)
вЂ‹Open Support Ticket
вЂ‹System Maintenance Mode (Toggle)
вЂ‹5. Visual Polish:
вЂ‹Use a light gray background (#F9FAFB) for the dashboard area to make the white cards pop.
вЂ‹Ensure every mention of a Company or Website is a functional OrangeLink.
вЂ‹Add "Skeleton Loaders" that show for 0.5s when the dashboard first loads to give it that premium SaaS feel.
